PROJECT: Cosmic Project Hub - AI-powered project management system

TECH STACK:
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + Realtime)
- Tailwind CSS (Cosmic theme)
- React Query (data fetching)
- Zustand (client state)
- Framer Motion (animations)

CODE STYLE:
- TypeScript strict mode (no 'any' types)
- Functional components with hooks
- Server/Client components separation
- Named exports over default exports
- Descriptive variable names
- Comments for complex logic

COSMIC THEME:
- Background: #0a0e1a (deep space)
- Surface: #151b2e (cosmic navy)
- Primary: #00d9ff (cyan neon)
- Secondary: #a855f7 (purple nebula)
- Accent: #ff6b35 (orange supernova)
- Fonts: Orbitron (display), Space Grotesk (body)

DATABASE:
- Use snake_case for columns
- Use camelCase in TypeScript
- Always use RLS policies
- Never bypass RLS in code
- Use Supabase client functions

BEST PRACTICES:
- Always validate user input (zod)
- Handle errors gracefully
- Show loading states
- Use optimistic updates
- Log errors to console
- Comment complex logic
- Write semantic HTML
- Accessibility (ARIA labels)

FORBIDDEN:
- No inline styles (use Tailwind)
- No CSS-in-JS libraries
- No external state management (only Zustand)
- No bypassing RLS
- No storing secrets in code
- No 'any' types

WORKFLOW:
- Read phase documentation fully
- Implement files in order
- Test after each major feature
- Commit frequently with clear messages
- Check for TypeScript errors
- Check for console errors

When implementing, follow the phase documents exactly and ask for clarification if unsure.
